在cwbplot套件使用colorbar設定¶

因為只是簡易範例，圖都沒有使用投影XD¶

import numpy as np

rainfall = np.load("/home/c052/work/opendata/21080606/rainfall.npy")
t2m = np.load("/home/c052/work/opendata/21080606/t2m.npy")
ygrids, xgrids = rainfall.shape
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.linspace(0, xgrids-1, xgrids),np.linspace(0,ygrids-1, ygrids))
In [35]:
#-defaultwrf team
import cwbplot.cwb_colorbar as cwbcolor #import cwbcolorbar 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

raincb = cwbcolor.rain() #rain()colorbar
plt.contourf(xx, yy, rainfall, **raincb)

#colorbartick label
cbstr = [ str(i) for i in raincb["levels"][1:-1]] 
cbar = plt.colorbar(ticks=raincb["levels"][1:-1])
newticks = cbar.ax.set_yticklabels(cbstr)
In [3]:
#colorbar
raincb = cwbcolor.rain() #rain()colorbar
plt.contourf(xx, yy, rainfall, **raincb)

#colorbartick label
cbstr = [ str(i) for i in raincb["levels"][1:-1]] 
cbar = plt.colorbar(ticks=raincb["levels"][1:-1],orientation="horizontal")
newticks = cbar.ax.set_xticklabels(cbstr)
In [4]:
#-wrf team19
newlevel = [0,0.1,5,10,30,50,80,100,150,200,300,350,400,
            500,600,800,1000,1250,1500]
raincb = cwbcolor.rain(colorlevel=newlevel) #rain()colorbar
ctf = plt.contourf(xx, yy, rainfall, **raincb)

cbstr = [ str(i) for i in raincb["levels"][1:-1]] 
cbar = plt.colorbar(ctf,ticks=raincb["levels"][1:-1])
newticks = cbar.ax.set_yticklabels(cbstr)

In [33]:
#colorbar ()
radarcb = cwbcolor.radar() #radar()colorbar
ctf = plt.contourf(xx, yy, rainfall/8, **radarcb, extend='both') 
ctf.cmap.set_under('None')
ctf.cmap.set_over('indigo')
cbar = plt.colorbar(ctf,drawedges=True) #drawedgesTrue
cbar.outline.set_edgecolor("slategray") #colorbar 
cbar.outline.set_linewidth(0.2) #colorbar 
cbar.dividers.set_color("white") #colorbar 
cbar.dividers.set_linewidth(2) #colorbar
